":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"le","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Lewis   or respelling of   Lou  , as borne by the impresario  Lew Grade  (  1906–98 , originally  Louis Winogradsky )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":6,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":19,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":73,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas le Maisterson was born in 1309, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England, his father, Robert le Maisterson, was 26 and his mother, Agnes Wilbrugham, was 3. He married Catherine Dutton in 1373, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died after 1422."},"et":{"1309–after 1422":"1309–pärast 1422","1309–1422":"1309–1422","1311–1331":"1311–1331","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1315–1349":"1315–1349","1317–1351":"1317–1351","1349–1396":"1349–1396","–1396":"–1396","1312–1370":"1312–1370","1374–1447":"1374–1447","1376–Male":"1376–Surnud","1284–Male":"1284–Surnud","1306–1370":"1306–1370","1374":"1374","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1351":"1351","1284":"1284","Bef 1312":"enne 1312","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1349":"1349","1447":"1447","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1312":"1312","1422":"1422","1311":"1311","1376":"1376","1331":"1331","about 1376":"umbes 1376","1309":"1309","after 1422":"pärast 1422","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","of Nantwich,Cheshire,England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1309–after 1422":"1309–1422 jälkeen","1309–1422":"1309–1422","1311–1331":"1311–1331","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1315–1349":"1315–1349","1317–1351":"1317–1351","1349–1396":"1349–1396","–1396":"–1396","1312–1370":"1312–1370","1374–1447":"1374–1447","1376–Male":"1376–Kuollut","1284–Male":"1284–Kuollut","1306–1370":"1306–1370","1374":"1374","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","1351":"1351","1284":"1284","Bef 1312":"ennen vuotta 1312","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1349":"1349","1447":"1447","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1312":"1312","1422":"1422","1311":"1311","1376":"1376","1331":"1331","about 1376":"noin 1376","1309":"1309","after 1422":"1422 jälkeen","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","of Nantwich,Cheshire,England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta